• Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above CAPE TOWN - Triple murder-accused Henri van Breda has taken the stand. Van Breda is accused of killing his mother, father and brother and seriously injuring his sister. READ: Van Breda murder trial postponed He is accused of murdering his parents and brother at their home in 2015. Van Breda says he heard strange sounds while in the bathroom went to investigate their source. "I could tell the sounds were coming from that room and I could see the silhouette of someone who appeared to be hitting Rudi," he testified. Defence advocate Pieter Botha requested that Van Breda’s testimony not be broadcast live as he suffers from a speech impediment. eNCA